Following full text Federal Reserve Board Chairman Paul Volcker's letter President Reagan decline reappointment Fed: Dear Mr. President As term chairman Federal Reserve Board approach naturally consider appropriate appointment. In connection recall reappointment chairman 1983 I unable firm commitment Congress remain office full four-year term. Despite reservation term finished. However I eight chairman natural return private soon reasonably convenient consistent orderly transition. Consequently I desire reappointment chairman I plan resign governor chairman prepared assume office. I leave appreciation unfailing courtesy personally. More broadly consistent support Federal Reserve particularly challenge period financial economy critical whatever success had. Without doubt strong challenge remain involve economic policy. In effort I believe nation continue serve strong Federal Reserve System -- firmly dedicate foster economic financial strength stability able bring effort combination sound independent professional judgement continuity beyond partisan considerations. May I add personal wish remainder term office restore confidence self-reliance American people. Faithfully yours Paul A Volcker Reuter 